"{\"uid\": \"egyptindependent.com-paris-olympics-apologizes-for-controversial-last-supper-parody\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"A member of the organizing committee of theParis 2024 Olympic Games,Anne Deschamps, apologized on Sunday for any offense that may have been caused by the opening ceremony of the Olympics, especially a scene that depicts the Greek god Dionysus alongside drag queens in the middle of a table.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 290, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 49, \"end\": 67, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"2024 Olympic Games\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 224, \"end\": 229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.9876560063348233, \"rank\": 0.009392514492332847, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}, {\"begin\": 234, \"end\": 242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1139880166560508e-13, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The scene was a parody of the Last Supper by the famous artist Leonardo da Vinci about Jesus Christ, but with the Olympics version including LGBT members instead.\", \"from\": 292, \"to\": 454, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 355, \"end\": 372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.360828067192856e-18, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 379, \"end\": 391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9995928823431299, \"rank\": 0.00040728345502721115, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 433, \"end\": 437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"score\": 0.9991758969902911, \"rank\": 0.0005690036753093472, \"text\": \"LGBT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Deschamps said: \\\"It is clear that we never intended to show disrespect to any religious group, and on the contrary I see that Thomas Jolly, the artistic director of the ceremony, wanted to celebrate societal tolerance, and we believe that this ambition was achieved.\", \"from\": 456, \"to\": 722, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 582, \"end\": 588, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.9999534676661825, \"rank\": 2.5107070516945624e-05, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If people felt any offense, we are very sorry for that.\\\"\", \"from\": 723, \"to\": 779, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly denied on Sunday that one of the performances was \\\"inspired\\\" by the painting of the Last Supper, following shock and outrage among far-right circles and the Catholic Church.\", \"from\": 781, \"to\": 960, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 944, \"end\": 959, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999797622751103, \"rank\": 2.0071551983523415e-05, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Joly told French news broadcast network BFMTV: \\\"I have absolutely no desire to ridicule or distort anything.\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 1070, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 972, \"end\": 978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9798701751636386, \"rank\": 0.020032882926054176, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1002, \"end\": 1007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BFM_TV\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"BFMTV\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BFM_TV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BFM_TV\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I wanted to have an opening ceremony that was reformative and reconciling, and that reaffirmed the values \\u200b\\u200bof our republic.\\\"\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1196, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With the growing criticism, the official video of the opening ceremony of the Paris 2024 Olympics has been removed from the tournament's YouTube account.\", \"from\": 1198, \"to\": 1351, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The American company C Spire also decided to withdraw its advertisements from the Olympic Games, due to the mockery of the Last Supper during the ceremonies in Paris.\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1519, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1353, \"end\": 1373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Old_American_Company\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The American company\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Old_American_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Old_American_Company\"}, {\"begin\": 1374, \"end\": 1381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/C_Spire\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"C Spire\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/C_Spire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/C_Spire\"}, {\"begin\": 1513, \"end\": 1518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999992031617686, \"rank\": 7.968388414867546e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An Al-Azhar Al-Sharif condemned the scene, and warned in its statement on social media of the danger of exploiting global events to normalize mocking religion and promote LGBT ideals.\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1704, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1692, \"end\": 1696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"score\": 0.9991758969902911, \"rank\": 0.0005690036753093472, \"text\": \"LGBT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\"}]}]}"